cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the connectivity of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) to cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the effects of antenna configurations on the performance of cellular-connected UAVs, which involves the study of information transmission and reception, making it relevant to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the control and management of UAVs in a cellular network, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve the transmission of multimedia data from UAVs to the ground station, making it relevant to multimedia. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of mobile UAVs, which falls under the domain of robotics.
